  "body": "\r\nSharing Template With subcharts, a feature documented in the [chart template guide](https://github.com/kubernetes/helm/blob/master/docs/chart_template_guide/subcharts_and_globals.md#sharing-templates-with-subcharts), appears to be inconsistent on which template will be used.\r\n\r\n**Problem:**\r\n\r\nIf you have the same named template in both a parent and sub chart, it is random which template will be used.\r\n\r\n**Why:**\r\n\r\nTemplates are being iterated and parsed in random order, (how golang's map/range works) here: https://github.com/kubernetes/helm/blob/master/pkg/engine/engine.go#L185\r\n\r\nAnd it doesn't appear there is anything in place that is meant to ensure the parent templates override the subcharts.",
